## Safety Note

<Callout type="info" title="ADHD Treatment: Comprehensive Approach">
Exercise is a valuable **adjunct** to evidence-based ADHD treatment — which includes medication (stimulants or non-stimulants), behavioral therapy, and environmental accommodations.

**Do not discontinue or reduce ADHD medication** based on exercise alone. Medication decisions should involve your prescribing clinician.

If you have ADHD and want to integrate exercise into your management plan, discuss it with your healthcare provider. They can help you optimize timing (e.g., exercise + medication synergy) and monitor symptom changes.
</Callout>
